				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "### I: A blind oracle of hegemony"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-06-09T21:51:50.359391+02:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-06-09T21:55:13.335803+02:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "hTnTpYrzDQCcuy5eBRKL7w=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "LLMs are nothing if not addicted to the average. This is by design, as a good statistical model is always centered—figuratively and literally—around the average. And so, if you ask a middle-of-the-road question, you will get a middle-of-the-road answer, since an LLM, unless explicitly prompted to do so, will not randomly decide to become agent provocateur and challenge all your ideas about the world. Usually, that is a good idea."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-06-09T21:55:32.531941+02:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-06-09T21:58:18.666807+02:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "MQD0sYrzDQConoATBRKL7w=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Why is this important? In most settings now, I see people approach the LLM as an all-knowing oracle, because in some respects it almost is. They hand it their problem (usually relatively sizable), and expect it to be solved. If you do not believe me that anyone would just go into an interaction so unprepared, just watch people vibe code."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-06-09T21:58:27.832374+02:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-06-09T22:00:15.789784+02:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "h1ggvYrzDQCzq7X4BRKL7w=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "What people do not realize, though, is that the oracle is mostly concerned with averages, and so it will give you a middle-of-the-road solution, if it is a functional solution at all. It was trained to be middle-of-the-road. Being middle-of-the-road is usually a good enough answer, even if noone wants to be described as such, for equally good reason."
			},
